39 (b) Employment Related Expenses. – The amount of employment-related expenses for
40 which a credit may be claimed may not exceed three thousand dollars ($3,000) if the taxpayer's
41 household includes one qualifying individual, as defined in section 21(b)(1) of the Code, and
42 may not exceed six thousand dollars ($6,000) if the taxpayer's household includes more than one
43 qualifying individual. The amount of employment-related expenses for which a credit may be
44 claimed is reduced by the amount of employer-provided dependent care assistance excluded from
45 gross income.
46 (c) Limitations. – A nonresident or part-year resident who claims the credit allowed by
47 this section shall reduce the amount of the credit by multiplying it by the fraction calculated under
48 G.S. 105-134.5(b) or (c), G.S. 105-153.4(b) or (c), as appropriate. No credit shall be allowed
49 under this section for amounts deducted in calculating North Carolina taxable income. The credit
50 allowed by this section may not exceed the amount of tax imposed by this Part for the taxable
